        <div class="cover-title">Social Scheduling <span style="opacity:0.6">·</span> Tools</div>
        <div class="cover-sub">10 Tested · Free → $249/mo · 90-day window</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="post-body-wrap">
    <div class="post-grid">
      <article class="post-content">
        <p class="lede-p">"Social media scheduling tools" covers two products that get sold as one. <strong>Schedulers</strong> (Buffer, Later, Publer) queue posts you already wrote. <strong>Done-for-you platforms</strong> (theStacc) write the posts and schedule them. Buying a scheduler when your real bottleneck is writing is the most common social SaaS mistake we see.</p>

        <p>We tested 10 tools across the spectrum over 90 days — solo creator queues, agency inboxes, evergreen recyclers, and full done-for-you services. Here is the ranking by what each tool actually replaces.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-tldr">
          <div class="callout-label">⚡ TL;DR — Pick by your bottleneck</div>
          <p><strong>You write posts, want to queue them:</strong> Buffer ($6/channel) or Publer (free tier). <strong>You manage clients and inboxes:</strong> Agorapulse or Sprout Social. <strong>You want posts written + scheduled without you in the loop:</strong> theStacc Social Media ($49/mo, fully done-for-you).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Don't want to write posts — just want them live?</h4>
            <p>theStacc writes, designs, and schedules posts to Instagram, LinkedIn, X, and Facebook. <strong>One bill, no calendar to fill</strong> — Social Media module starts at $49/mo.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">See a live demo <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">No card · 15-min walkthrough</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="what-is">The 4 categories of social media scheduling tools</h2>
        <p>Every "scheduler" falls into one of four buckets. Buy by the bucket you actually need:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Solo creator queues</strong> — Buffer, Publer, Pallyy. Simple calendar + publish to a few channels.</li>
          <li><strong>Agency dashboards</strong> — Hootsuite, Agorapulse, Sendible, SocialPilot. Multi-client, inboxes, approvals.</li>
          <li><strong>Visual-first planners</strong> — Later, Loomly, Metricool. Grid previews, media library, design-led.</li>
          <li><strong>Done-for-you services</strong> — theStacc Social Media. Posts written, designed, and scheduled for you.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">⚠️ The scheduler trap</div>
          <p>A scheduler saves you the publishing minutes. It does nothing about the writing hours. If your team is skipping posts because nobody has time to write them, buying Hootsuite at $99/mo will not fix that — you will just have an empty calendar inside a more expensive tool.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested all 10 tools</h2>
        <p>Same brand kit, same posting cadence, same 90-day window across three industries.</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Test brands</strong> — 3 fresh accounts in SaaS, ecom, and local service.</li>
          <li><strong>Scope</strong> — 60 posts per tool across IG, LinkedIn, X, and Facebook over 90 days.</li>
          <li><strong>Measurement</strong> — time-to-publish, network coverage, failed posts, total cost.</li>
          <li><strong>Total spend</strong> — $2,140 across 10 tools, Mar–May 2026.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What we measured</h3>
        <div class="stat-grid">
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">10</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Tools tested</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">Across all 4 categories</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">90</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Day window</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">Mar–May 2026</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">$2.1K</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Total spend</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">Across all tools</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">3</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Industries</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">SaaS · Ecom · Local</div>
