          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do social media schedulers actually save time?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes — for scheduling. Schedulers save roughly 4-6 hours per week on publishing. They do not save you the writing time, which is usually 70% of the work. A done-for-you platform that writes and schedules removes both halves.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between scheduling and publishing?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Scheduling means queueing posts in a calendar. Publishing means the post actually goes live on the network. Most tools schedule directly through official APIs (Instagram, LinkedIn, Facebook, X). A few still rely on push notifications for Instagram personal accounts — check before you buy.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can a scheduler replace a social media manager?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For execution, partially. The scheduler handles queueing and publishing. It does not write, ideate, or respond to comments. A done-for-you platform that bundles content creation with scheduling replaces about 80% of the social media manager role for SMBs.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How many posts per week should I schedule?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
